               <head>Sefer ha-ziḳuḳ by Dominico Irosolimitano</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85021830" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A collection of notes and lists for the censorship of Hebrew books. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="136v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-ziḳuḳ</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">ספר הזקוק</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>In a form begun by Dominico Irosolomitano in 1597, and continued later with entries of books printed down to 1612. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The book itself is preceded by the following sections: 1. folios 2r-3r, a list of special anti-Christian passages to be noted by a censor; 2. folios 3r-3v, notes on the healing power of the precious stones names in Ex. 28:17-20; 3. folios 3v-13r, an alphabetical index of the books names in the work itself, under the following heading in Italian and Hebrew: 'Tauola di tutti li libri qui segnati per Aplhabeto'; 4. folio 13r, a memorandum (apparently taken from a note of Irosolomitano) of books and manuscripts examined for censorship in different places. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Sefer ha-ziḳuḳ begins on folio 14r (where the original Hebrew foliation commences). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>See further <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">81 ff.</ref>; <ref target="Porges_1903" type="page">273-295</ref>; <ref target="Sonne_1943" type="page">975-1015</ref>. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/97204542">Irosolimitano, Dominico </persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/97204542">דומיניקו, ירושלמי</persName>
                     
                     
                     
